<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_142c6992-033f-4802-b388-e300114bf7e4" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/><facet climate="Climate zone 8"/></meta><sptc>5.5.2</sptc><title id="_b5915911-8eb0-462b-92fd-1b79e05b807a">Isolated piers supporting carports, verandahs, porches and similar roof structures</title><archive-num>2019: 3.3.6.2</archive-num><subclause id="_965b6b97-11fa-411a-b910-558620acb1dd" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a3da3749-59a5-425e-b5cd-3ba348fd7ea3">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Isolated piers supporting carports, verandahs, porches and similar roof structures, or vehicle access door openings, which form part of the main roof, or are attached to a wall of a Class 1 building must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a2d2fbca-68d1-4aa3-9d3d-0771d0e2c011">be not less than 290 x 290 mm in section; and</li><li id="_dd484fb8-2389-4b7b-b7e3-796d4411a100">be not more than 2.7 m high (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/608_0.9.0.xml#_5cdded45-2b64-41d9-aa40-dda6e0ba8c64" id="_f295ee26-baf4-4003-8721-a0b9b343b15a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 5.5.2</xref>); and</li><li id="_112b406c-34c3-43a7-81a5-92790e982b1c">be spaced at not more than 3 m centres (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/608_0.9.0.xml#_5cdded45-2b64-41d9-aa40-dda6e0ba8c64" id="_08496aca-4c94-4d1d-965f-fece8500ba6d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 5.5.2</xref>); and</li><li id="_e1a64180-be39-416f-878c-2c446505bfda">provide a bearing length of not less than 150 mm for any supported members; and</li><li id="_7e13f006-9f24-4807-8c81-97bd60d61900">comply with the relevant provisions of this Part.</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/608_0.9.0.xml" id="_5cdded45-2b64-41d9-aa40-dda6e0ba8c64"><num>5.5.2</num><title id="_f7be93dd-ae27-4c77-9e55-c4403cbd4ab6">Piers under main roof</title><image alt="Piers under main roof" height="601" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:5-5-2-piers-under-main-roof.eps" width="1190" widthdpi="200"><image height="601" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_74388e36-9e93-4536-8dde-523b004b18a5.jpg" width="1190" widthdpi="200"/></image></image-reference></clause>